<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-08-24T02:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-08-24T02:00:00-05:00" n="581" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d581">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.5294/500: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-08-24T16:00:00+09:00">August 24, 1934—4
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received August 24—9 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>189. Department’s 143, August 22, 5 p.m., Arizona incident.</p>
                        <list>
                            <label>1.</label>
                            <item>I brought pertinent facts today to the attention of the Vice
                                Minister for Foreign Affairs who assured me of cooperation of
                                Foreign <pb facs="0782" n="692" xml:id="pg_692"/> Office in
                                discouraging sensational discussion and expressed appreciation of
                                Department’s efforts.</item>
                            <label>2.</label>
                            <item>There appears as yet to have been no sensational or agitated
                                comments in the Japanese press which has in general confined itself
                                to a mere report of the facts.</item>
                        </list>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>